  "_stage_zone_structure": {
    "finding": "10 ST*.DAT stage groups (ST0-ST9) vs 10 canonical zones. Zone ROOM names are now in map.json (XGameMania, Japanese+English).",
    "st_room_counts": {
      "ST0": 6,
      "ST1": 17,
      "ST2": 6,
      "ST3": 7,
      "ST4": 12,
      "ST5": 5,
      "ST6": 9,
      "ST7": 8,
      "ST8": 12,
      "ST9": 7
    },
    "zone_room_counts (XGameMania)": {
      "Jungle": 16,
      "Military Facility": 6,
      "Patrol Ship": 2,
      "Research Facility": 7,
      "3rd Energy Facility": 9,
      "3rd Energy Reactor": 12,
      "Areaway to City": 11,
      "Edward City": 5,
      "Missile Silo": 8,
      "Habitat Support Facility": 8
    },
    "count_match_attempt": "Matching ST counts to zone counts does NOT yield a clean bijection: ST1(17)~Jungle(16) is the one strong unique match, and ST6(9)~3rd Energy Facility(9) / ST5(5)~Edward City(5) are exact-but-not-unique. The rest collide (ST0&ST2 both =6 like Military; ST4&ST8 both =12 like 3rd Energy Reactor; ST3&ST9 both =7 like Research) AND two zones have no matching ST count (Patrol Ship=2, Areaway to City=11), because a guide 'sub-area' is not 1:1 with an ST*.DAT file (e.g. Patrol Ship lists only 2 player-relevant rooms; revisits reuse files).",
    "status": "RESOLVED 2026-06-28 (byte). ST->zone = A2Z[area_id(stage,room)], area_id = Dino2.exe fn 0x491c70, A2Z = the 0x49d770 area-name array. ST4 is the only split stage (rooms 0-6,11=Missile Silo; 7-10=Habitat). The ST-file room counts differ from the XGameMania 'player-relevant' sub-area counts (4 zones match EXACT, 3 differ by 1) because a guide sub-area is not 1:1 with an ST*.DAT file; the EXE mapping is authoritative.",
    "how_to_resolve": "Read the on-screen AREA name while loading each ST file in-game (or via emulator save states); or decode a zone/BGM id inside the room blob; or RAM-dump the stage variable in a known area. Any single confirmed ST->room anchor per zone would let the XGameMania room lists be aligned to ST ids.",
    "resolution": "docs/dc2/ZONE-MAPPING-RE.md; materialized per-room in room-data.json and here via tools/dc2_re/backfill_zones.py."
  }
